5000|$|For {{statistical}} purposes, {{investment in}} fixed capital must {{be distinguished from}} investment in <b>intermediate</b> <b>goods.</b> Unlike fixed assets, <b>intermediate</b> <b>goods</b> (for example, commodities like oil, electricity, timber, steel and grain) are completely used up in production (usually within a year). But this distinction {{is not always easy}} to draw, for example: ...|$|E
